What if checkpoint storage (S3) fails?
Impact: checkpoints cannot be saved , fault tolerance breaks
Flink behavior:job continues temporarily, checkpointing fails repeatedly, eventually job may restart or degrade
Mitigation:retries, multi-AZ S3, backup checkpoint location, alerting on checkpoint failure

Exactly-once in full pipeline (Kafka → Flink → DB)
End-to-end design: Kafka: retains offsets
Flink:checkpoint state + offsets
Sink:must support one of: idempotent writes, transactional writes

